    "name": "Cyril Neville",
    "profile": "One of the four Neville Brothers, Cyril Neville was the youngest, born on January 10, 1948, in New Orleans, Louisiana, USA. Cyril picked up his love of music from his parents and his older brothers at an early age, but it wasn't until 1967 (at the age of 19) that Cyril began singing professionally, as he united with brothers [url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/294571-Art-Neville]Art[/url] and [url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/15261-Aaron-Neville]Aaron[/url] in the group Art Neville And The Neville Sounds, playing the New Orleans club circuit on a regular basis. Cyril and Aaron eventually left and formed Soul Machine, shortly thereafter. 1970 saw the release of Cyril's debut solo single, [i]Gossip[/i] b/w [i]Tell Me What's On Your Mind[/i], which included backing music by brother Art's new outfit, [a86616]. Soul Machine relocated to Nashville, then New York City, but both moves failed to help put the group on the top. It just so happened at this time that the Meters were looking to ex",
